          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "AM-BE"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Am/Be neutron source from the Department",
                "of Applied Chemistry and Chemical Technology of the",
                "Rajshahi University. The active  component (A)",
                "consists of the alpha-emitting radionuclide 241Am",
                " (activity 111 GBq in 1977) alloyed with Be,and sealed",
                "in a  cylindrical metal capsule which was then",
                "covered by a graphite  layer to avoid any leak of the",
                "activity",
                "Considering the distance and the solid angle subtended",
                "by a sample at two positions, the flux density at that",
                "position was estimated to be 1.5 x 10**5 n/cm2/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "High-purity foils of several metals were cut in",
                "circular discs (dia. 2 cm) and irradiated either",
                "individually or together in a stack.  The choice of a",
                "foil depended on the nuclear reaction induced in it.",
                " The foils covered three energy regions of the neutron",
                "spectrum, viz. thermal, low-energy(<1.5 MeV)and high",
                "energy (>1.5 MeV).  Several stacks of Fe, Co, Ni and Mo",
                "foils were prepared and irradiated in various positions",
                "The duration of each irradiation was about 300h.",
                " Au and In foils, on the other hand, were irradiated",
                "individually, each for about 24h, without placing the",
                "active component in the paraffin shielding."
              ]
            }
          ],
